name: Streadata.io API Gallery - Google Cloud Storage
description: This is a repository of google cloud storage APIs, self-contained as a Github repository, with HTML and YAML representations of the APIs and their surrounding operations.

apis.name: Google Cloud Storage
apis.description: Google Cloud Storage is unified object storage for developers and enterprises, from live data serving to data analytics/ML to data archiving. Google Cloud Storage allows world-wide storage and retrieval of any amount of data at any time. You can use Google Cloud Storage for a range of scenarios including serving website content, storing data for archival and disaster recovery, or distributing large data objects to users via direct download.
